ext_description.note:
		The ability is provided in this part of ISO 10303 to state:


passage passes through stratum on each end;


				passage passes through stratum on top end but passes through stratum adjacent
				to stratum on bottom end (i.e. the passage "touches" the stratum on bottom end.);



				passage passes through stratum adjacent to stratum on top end (i.e. the
				passage "touches" the stratum on top end.) and passes through stratum on bottom end;



				passage passes through stratum adjacent to top end and passes through stratum
				adjacent to bottom end(i.e., touches the top and bottom stratum).
